## Delivery Rules

- Do not start large implementation while blocking `[To confirm]` items remain unresolved.
- If there is a material ambiguity about requirements, architecture direction, stack choice, data model, or test coverage strategy, confirm it with the user before deciding.
- New features must update the affected workflow, knowledge, verification, and task docs together.
- API, data shape, and config changes must update design docs, knowledge docs, and tests together.
- Bug fixes must include regression tests and a corresponding change workspace update.
- New requirements, bug fixes, refactors, or workflow changes should update `docs/changes/active/` or its archive destinations.
- Releases or externally visible delivery changes should update `docs/releases/`.
- Unresolved issues, risks, and technical debt should update `docs/issues/`.
- Replaced or retired documents should be moved into `docs/archive/`.
- Any structure change must update `README.md`, `spec-init.topology.yml`, and `docs/rules/document-routing-rules.md`.
- Record key technical trade-offs in `docs/adr/`.
- Every task should reference `FR-*`, `DES-*`, and `TEST-*` IDs.
- Mark uncertain information as `[To confirm]` instead of inventing it.
- Before implementation starts, ensure at least one complete chain exists: `FR -> DES -> TEST -> T`.
- When there is a more specific rule, follow the documents in `docs/rules/`.

