## Definition of Done

- Requirements, design, verification, and tasks are traceable.
- Long-lived truths are documented under `docs/knowledge/`.
- The current change is recorded in the correct location under `docs/changes/active/`, `completed/`, or `legacy/`.
- Code and docs stay in sync.
- High-priority requirements have automated verification.
- README helps new contributors understand the structure quickly.
- Known trade-offs and risks are recorded in docs or ADRs.
- The checklist in `docs/rules/definition-of-done.md` passes.
